SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1736
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR WASHINGTON.
7403S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To amend chapter 163, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to state aid allocations
to certain school districts.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Chapter 163, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto
2 one new section, to be known as section 163.039, to read as
3 follows:
1 163.039. 1. Notwithstanding the provisions of section
2 163.031 and 163.044 to the contrary, beginning in school
3 year 2026-27 and for each subsequent school year, none of
4 the following school districts shall receive state aid
5 calculated under subsection 2 of section 163.031, and no
6 such district shall receive any funds under section 163.044:
7 (1) A school district whose boundaries wholly
8 encompass a village with more than sixty but fewer than
9 sixty-seven inhabitants and located in a county with more
10 than seven thousand but fewer than eight thousand
11 inhabitants and with a county seat with fewer than four
12 hundred eighty inhabitants;
13 (2) A school district whose boundaries wholly
14 encompass a city with more than four hundred thirty but
15 fewer than four hundred eighty inhabitants and that is the
16 county seat of a county with more than seven thousand but
17 fewer than eight thousand inhabitants;

