138 4. For purposes of this section only, "local effort"
139 shall mean the following calculation: For each fiscal year
140 calculation, local effort shall be computed as the equalized
141 assessed valuation of the property of a school district in
142 calendar year 2024 divided by one hundred and multiplied by
143 the performance levy less the percentage retained by the
144 county assessor and collector plus one hundred percent of

SB 1736 6
145 the amount received in fiscal year 2025 for school purposes
146 from intangible taxes, fines, escheats, payments in lieu of
147 taxes and receipts from state-assessed railroad and utility
148 tax, one hundred percent of the amount received for school
149 purposes pursuant to the merchants' and manufacturers' taxes
150 under sections 150.010 to 150.370, one hundred percent of
151 the amounts received for school purposes from federal
152 properties under sections 12.070 and 12.080 except when such
153 amounts are used in the calculation of federal impact aid
154 pursuant to Pub. L. 81-874, fifty percent of Proposition C
155 revenues received for school purposes from the school
156 district trust fund under section 163.087, and one hundred
157 percent of any local earnings or income taxes received by
158 the district for school purposes.
